            "summary": "Kids find a mysterious door in a concert hall that leads to living music",
            "text": "The old concert hall smells like velvet and history. {{PLAYER1_NAME}} and {{PLAYER2_NAME}} are here for a backstage tour with the youth orchestra, but somehow they've gotten separated from the group.\n\n'I think we went the wrong way,' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} says, looking at a long corridor they don't recognize.\n\nAt the end of the corridor is a door that seems to glow faintly. Musical notes‚Äîactual glowing notes‚Äîdrift from underneath it.\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} pushes the door open.\n\nInside is a room that can't exist‚Äîit's much bigger than the building itself. Grand pianos float in midair. Violins play themselves. And strangest of all, music is visible here‚Äîribbons of color flowing through the air, each melody a different hue.\n\n'Welcome to the Symphony Eternal,' says a voice. A woman in an elegant 18th-century gown glides toward them. 'I am the Muse of Music. You've found the place where great compositions live forever. Would you like to meet their creators?'",
