        "music-basics": {
            "id": "music-basics",
            "summary": "The Muse explains the basic elements of music",
            "text": "'What makes music... music?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks.\n\nThe Muse smiles and waves her hand. The colored ribbons of melody swirl around them.\n\n'Music has four essential elements. First: melody‚Äîthe tune, the part you hum.' A golden ribbon flows past, and they hear a familiar song. 'It's a sequence of notes that tells a story.\n\n'Second: rhythm‚Äîthe heartbeat of music.' A drum appears, and {{PLAYER2_NAME}} feels their foot tapping automatically. 'Fast or slow, steady or syncopated, rhythm makes us want to move.\n\n'Third: harmony‚Äînotes played together.' She plays a chord on a nearby piano‚Äîthree notes at once that blend beautifully. 'Harmony adds depth, emotion, richness.\n\n'Fourth: timbre‚Äîthe color of sound.' She plays the same note on piano, then violin, then flute. 'Same pitch, but each sounds completely different. That unique voice is timbre.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} watches the colors pulse with each element. 'Music is like... a language?'\n\n'The only language that needs no translation. Every human culture has music. It speaks directly to the soul.'",
