        "follow-melody": {
            "id": "follow-melody",
            "summary": "They follow a hauntingly beautiful melody to its source",
            "text": "One melody calls to {{PLAYER2_NAME}}‚Äîa silver ribbon of sound, achingly beautiful and sad. They follow it through floating instruments and swirling colors.\n\nThe ribbon leads to a young man sitting at a piano, eyes closed, playing with incredible feeling. His clothes are old-fashioned, his hair wild. He doesn't seem to hear them approach.\n\n'That's Beethoven,' the Muse whispers. 'He couldn't hear anything by the end of his life‚Äîhe was completely deaf. Yet he wrote some of the most powerful music in history.'\n\n'Deaf?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} is stunned. 'But how?'\n\n'He heard the music in his mind. When his ears failed, his inner hearing became stronger. He felt the vibrations, understood the mathematics of harmony, trusted his training and imagination.'\n\nBeethoven finishes and opens his eyes. They're deep and intense. 'You heard it?' he asks, his voice oddly flat‚Äîthe voice of someone who can't hear himself speak.\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} nods, tears unexpectedly forming. 'It was beautiful. So sad but so... hopeful?'\n\n'My Moonlight Sonata. Sadness and hope‚Äîyes, that is life. That is music.'",
