        "classical-wing": {
            "id": "classical-wing",
            "summary": "They enter a grand hall where famous composers work and teach",
            "text": "The Classical Wing is a grand hall filled with composers from across centuries. Each sits at their own station‚Äîpiano, writing desk, or instrument‚Äîcreating music that flows visibly through the air.\n\n'These are some of history's greatest musical minds,' the Muse says. 'Each changed how humans experience sound.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} recognizes some names on golden plaques: BACH, MOZART, BEETHOVEN, CHOPIN, TCHAIKOVSKY.\n\nA man in a powdered wig looks up from a complex musical score. 'Visitors! How delightful! I am Johann Sebastian Bach. I wrote music for the glory of God and the instruction of the soul.'\n\nNearby, a younger man in colorful clothing plays a playful melody. 'And I am Mozart! I wrote because music poured out of me like water from a fountain. I couldn't stop if I tried!'\n\nA serious-looking man nods curtly from the corner. 'Beethoven. I wrote because I had something to say.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} feels overwhelmed by so much genius in one room. 'Can we... talk to them?'",
