        "mozart-genius": {
            "id": "mozart-genius",
            "summary": "Mozart shares his effortless genius and playful approach",
            "text": "Mozart is playing a complicated piece while simultaneously having a conversation, occasionally pausing to write notes on a staff, all while humming a completely different tune.\n\n'How do you do that?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks, amazed.\n\n'Do what?' Mozart looks genuinely confused. 'Oh, the multiple things? I cannot help it! Music is always playing in my head. Multiple pieces at once, sometimes. When I was four, I picked out tunes on the harpsichord. By five, I was composing. By six, I was performing for emperors.'\n\n'So you were born a genius?'\n\nMozart's playful expression grows thoughtful. 'I was born with an ear for music, yes. But I also practiced constantly. My father taught me from before I could walk. What looks like effortless talent is thousands of hours of work that started so young I don't remember not doing it.'\n\nHe plays a joyful melody. 'But I'll tell you a secret: I never felt like work. Music is play for me. The luckiest thing is not being talented‚Äîit's loving something enough to want to do it forever.'",
