        "jazz-room": {
            "id": "jazz-room",
            "summary": "They experience improvisation and the spontaneous creation of jazz",
            "text": "The Jazz Room is smoky and intimate. Musicians sit in a circle, passing melodies back and forth like a conversation.\n\nA man with a trumpet looks up. 'Hey there, young cats! I'm Louis. Pull up a chair.'\n\n{{BOTH_NAMES}} sit and watch. A piano plays a melody. The trumpet picks it up, changes it, adds ornaments. A saxophone responds with something completely different but somehow related. A drummer keeps everything grounded while adding flourishes.\n\n'This is improvisation,' Louis explains between phrases. 'We're making it up as we go. No two performances are ever the same.'\n\n'But how do you know what to play?' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks.\n\n'We know the rules so well, we can break them. We know the chord progressions, the song structure. Inside that framework, we're free. It's like having a conversation‚Äîyou don't memorize what to say, but you follow the flow.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} hears how each musician listens to the others, responding, supporting, challenging. 'It's like they're reading each other's minds!'\n\n'Better than that‚Äîwe're listening. Really listening. That's the heart of jazz: paying attention to this moment, right now.'",
