            "summary": "They try their hand at improvising and learn to trust themselves",
            "text": "Louis hands {{PLAYER1_NAME}} a small xylophone. 'Nothing fancy. Just listen to what we're playing and add something. Anything.'\n\nThe band starts a slow blues. {{PLAYER1_NAME}}'s hands shake. What if {{PLAYER1_HE_SHE}} plays something wrong?\n\n'There's no wrong,' Louis says gently, sensing the fear. 'There's only interesting and less interesting. And even less interesting is part of the journey to interesting.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} tentatively taps a few notes. They sound... okay? The drummer gives an encouraging nod. {{PLAYER1_NAME}} tries a little pattern. The piano plays something underneath that makes it sound better.\n\n'You're listening!' Louis grins. 'That's the secret. Don't think so hard. Feel the music. Let it tell you where to go.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} tries next. At first just tapping along with the rhythm. Then a little melody emerges‚Äîsimple but real. The band supports it, makes it sound like part of the whole.\n\n'That's yours,' Louis says. 'Something that never existed before. You just made music. Nobody can take that away from you.'",
