            "text": "The World Music Garden is like stepping into every country at once. Beneath a baobab tree, African drummers play complex polyrhythms. Near a pagoda, a Chinese erhu sings. By a campfire, a didgeridoo drones while Aboriginal voices tell ancient stories.\n\n'Every culture creates music,' the Muse says. 'But every culture creates different music. Listen to how they approach melody, rhythm, harmony‚Äîall different, all beautiful.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} is drawn to the African drums. There seem to be ten different rhythms happening at once, but somehow they all fit together.\n\n'In West African drumming,' an older man explains, 'each rhythm is simple alone. But together, they create something none can make by themselves. Like a community‚Äîwe each contribute our part.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} listens to an Indian musician play ragas‚Äîmelodies that express specific times of day and emotions. 'This raga is for evening,' the musician says. 'It brings peace after the struggles of the day.'\n\nThe Muse smiles. 'Human beings are diverse, but our need for music is universal. Different languages, same yearning to express what words cannot.'",
