            "summary": "Master drummers teach about polyrhythm and community",
            "text": "The drum master invites {{BOTH_NAMES}} to sit. 'In my village, drums are not instruments. They are voices. They call people to gather, announce births and deaths, speak to ancestors, make work feel lighter.'\n\nHe gives each of them a small drum. 'Feel the skin. An animal gave this so we could make music. We honor that gift by playing with full hearts.'\n\nHe shows them a simple pattern: one-two, one-two. They follow. Then he adds a second pattern that weaves between theirs. Then a third person joins with something different. Soon there are five rhythms happening at once.\n\n'Each alone is simple,' the master says. 'Together, magic. This is why we play in groups. Music teaches us that we need each other. Your contribution matters‚Äîmiss your beat and everyone feels it. Stay true and you hold us all together.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} focuses, keeping the pattern steady. It's harder than it looks. But when it all clicks, when everyone is perfectly in sync... it feels like flying.\n\n'This is called entrainment,' the Muse explains. 'Rhythms aligning. Heartbeats sync too. Music literally brings people together.'",
