            "summary": "The Muse reveals how music has changed history and healed wounds",
            "text": "'Music is more than entertainment,' the Muse says seriously. 'It has changed the course of history.'\n\nShe shows them images: slave spirituals that gave hope and communicated escape routes. Protest songs that fueled civil rights movements. National anthems that united people. War drums that coordinated armies. Lullabies that soothed babies for a hundred thousand years.\n\n'Music heals too. Stroke patients who can't speak can sometimes sing. People with dementia remember songs from their youth when they remember nothing else. Veterans with trauma find peace through drumming circles.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} thinks about all the times music helped {{PLAYER1_HIM_HER}}‚Äîsad songs when sad, happy songs to celebrate, calming music when anxious.\n\n'Why is it so powerful?' {{PLAYER2_NAME}} asks.\n\n'Because it bypasses logic and speaks directly to feeling. You can argue with words. You can't argue with a melody that makes your heart swell. Music tells us we're not alone in our emotions‚Äîsomeone else felt this too, and turned it into something beautiful. That's profoundly comforting.'",
